10:49.441 --> 10:50.776
- Yeah, he's gonna thank us later.

10:50.776 --> 10:51.985
We'll have a laugh about it. Like--

10:51.985 --> 10:54.112
[laughing]

10:54.112 --> 10:55.656
I bet he's already learning--
[glass shatters]

10:55.656 --> 10:57.574
[all scream]
[tires squealing]

10:57.574 --> 10:59.576
- What the hell was that?
- Pupa and Little Buddy!

10:59.576 --> 11:02.037
JESSE: How did they get out
of military school so fast?

11:02.037 --> 11:03.914
KORVO: They made friends
with that hard-ass drill sergeant!

11:03.914 --> 11:06.375
- The Pupa's too charismatic!
People love his charm!

11:06.375 --> 11:09.419
- We should never have stopped for Terry
to hawk Stella & Dot to that brunch club!

11:09.419 --> 11:10.671
TERRY:
You can't talk to me like that.

11:10.671 --> 11:13.131
I'm 10K away from being
an associate ambassador.

11:14.883 --> 11:16.969
♪ dramatic music playing ♪

11:16.969 --> 11:21.056
♪

11:21.056 --> 11:23.267
♪

11:23.267 --> 11:25.018
[engine revving, tires squealing]

11:25.686 --> 11:29.189
♪

11:29.189 --> 11:32.442
♪

11:32.442 --> 11:35.362
♪

11:36.613 --> 11:38.198
[gunshot]
[motorcycle crashes]

11:38.991 --> 11:41.785
- Who's the Pupa expert now, bitch?

11:43.745 --> 11:45.664
- Okay, look, Pupa,
it's not that we're mad.

11:45.664 --> 11:48.166
We're just so disappointed in you.
You're better than this.

11:48.166 --> 11:49.710
- I don't get it.
We've tried everything!

11:49.710 --> 11:51.920
Tough love, soft love,
crazy stupid love--

11:51.920 --> 11:55.257
- We even had Courtney Love watch
Love Actually with you and nothing!

11:55.257 --> 11:58.218
- You were acting bad before but now
with Little Buddy, it's way worse.

11:58.218 --> 12:00.304
- Yeah, Little Buddy's
a bad influence.

12:00.304 --> 12:02.890
- Yes, Little Buddy's the problem.
Because it's definitely not us.

12:02.890 --> 12:04.224
- Little Buddy is my friend.

12:04.224 --> 12:07.436
- No! I forbid you from seeing
Little Buddy ever again! Get him, Terry.

12:07.436 --> 12:08.937
- Give me that Little Buddy!
Give him to me!

12:08.937 --> 12:10.480
- And to make sure he never comes back,

12:10.480 --> 12:12.524
I'm trapping him inside
of a crystal paperweight.

12:12.524 --> 12:13.775
- Yeah, budd--

12:14.568 --> 12:16.195
- No!

12:16.195 --> 12:19.281
- Now, he can't give you bad ideas,
and he'll keep our bills from flying away.

12:19.281 --> 12:21.366
- You know, Stella & Dot has
a dandelion paperweight--

12:21.366 --> 12:23.202
- Jesus fuck, Terry,
it's a pyramid scheme.

12:23.202 --> 12:26.371
[growling, snarling]

12:26.371 --> 12:29.208
- Alright, this is just a tantrum.
Let him tire himself out.

12:29.208 --> 12:31.084
Pretty soon, he'll be back
to normal and we can--

12:31.084 --> 12:32.127
[Pupa screams]

12:34.880 --> 12:37.257
- Oh! The pupa exploded into a mist!

12:37.257 --> 12:38.926
- It's not a mist.
- It's a fog.

12:38.926 --> 12:40.427
- No, it's more like a steam.

12:40.427 --> 12:44.223
- Whatever it is, we're trapped inside,
and it smells like the Pupa's ass!

12:45.224 --> 12:48.268
[people screaming]

12:51.772 --> 12:53.774
- Great, what a classic teenager way
to act out,

12:53.774 --> 12:56.401
turning himself into a blanket of steam
that hangs over the town.

12:56.401 --> 12:59.112
Pupa, you recombine
into your own physical form this instant!

12:59.112 --> 13:00.113
You hear me, mister?

13:00.113 --> 13:03.492
- No! Don't go that way!
There are monsters!

13:03.492 --> 13:05.536
- Great, now he's making monsters
in the steam.

13:05.536 --> 13:07.246
I told you we should have
gotten him into soccer.

13:07.246 --> 13:09.665
- Ohhh, I just saw
a tentacle over there.

13:09.665 --> 13:11.625
- The Pupa is such a bad teenager.
[monster growling]

13:11.625 --> 13:12.876
God, I wish I could be like him.

13:12.876 --> 13:13.877
- No, he sucks.

13:13.877 --> 13:15.712
Pupa, you're in a lot
of trouble, young man!

13:15.712 --> 13:19.049
You better stop being steam this instant
or... no more playing Roblox!

13:19.508 --> 13:20.592
[all scream]

13:21.802 --> 13:24.388
YUMYULACK: Was that steam monster
wearing a PewDiePie hoodie?

13:24.388 --> 13:26.723
- The Pupa's delinquency
must be manifesting

13:26.723 --> 13:28.100
as adolescent creatures.

13:28.100 --> 13:31.061
Look out! There's one wearing
Tech Fleece and listening to Future!

13:31.061 --> 13:32.896
[screaming]

13:35.023 --> 13:37.109
[panting]

13:38.318 --> 13:41.321
- Hey, guys. Geez, Ms. Frankie.
You work here, too?

13:41.321 --> 13:44.032
- [mimicking Jesse]
"Aw geez, you work here, too."

13:44.032 --> 13:45.409
Of course I don't, you idiot.

13:45.409 --> 13:46.994
- Not that it's any
of your business,

13:46.994 --> 13:48.829
but we're making ossobuco
for dinner!

13:48.829 --> 13:51.290
It pairs well with a night
of consensual edging.

13:52.624 --> 13:53.667
[screeches]

13:56.086 --> 13:57.129
[glass shatters]

13:57.129 --> 13:58.380
[cell phone buzzes]

14:01.842 --> 14:04.011
- Okay, it definitely seems like
they are teens,

14:04.011 --> 14:05.554
but somebody needs
to go out there and find out

14:05.554 --> 14:06.722
what we are really dealing with here.

14:06.722 --> 14:07.848
- Uh, no, we don't!

14:07.848 --> 14:09.850
These monsters are
all over TikTok.

14:09.850 --> 14:13.061
- That Pacific garbage patch is huge!

14:13.061 --> 14:16.148
- These monsters are expressing
all the Pupa's bad teen behavior.

14:16.148 --> 14:18.025
We better pray he's not one
of those arson kids.

14:18.025 --> 14:20.194
- I think the Pupa just needs a friend.

14:20.194 --> 14:22.237
Maybe if we can get home
and release Little Buddy,

14:22.237 --> 14:23.697
he'll stop misting himself.

14:23.697 --> 14:24.698
- You have a point.

14:24.698 --> 14:26.783
But if we let Little Buddy go,
all our bills might fly away.

14:26.783 --> 14:28.869
Ugh! What do we do?
What do we do?

14:29.411 --> 14:30.913
[screeches]
[all scream]

14:30.913 --> 14:32.748
- Come on, we can get to my car!

14:32.748 --> 14:34.583
- Who the fuck is this guy?
- I'm Desmond!

14:37.211 --> 14:38.629
- Quick, give me the breathalyzer!

14:38.629 --> 14:40.172
- Here. And also, wow.

14:40.172 --> 14:41.840
I'd like to hear the story behind that!
[breathalyzer beeps]

14:41.840 --> 14:44.218
- Aw, come on!
Point nine's my baseline!

14:44.218 --> 14:45.969
Who else can drive?
- Oh, let me try!

14:46.386 --> 14:47.429
[beeps]

14:47.429 --> 14:49.932
2.8! Yes!
Alcoholic high score!

14:49.932 --> 14:51.058
[beeps]

14:51.058 --> 14:52.392
I got this.

14:52.392 --> 14:56.522
- Wait! Sign my change-dot-org petition
to help de-stigmatize cyberbullying!

14:56.522 --> 14:57.648
- Whatever, man.

14:57.648 --> 14:59.816
- You just don't get it!
- No cap!

14:59.816 --> 15:02.319
- I'm not sus, you're sus!

15:02.319 --> 15:03.946
[tires squealing]

15:03.946 --> 15:04.988
- Word, lit!

15:05.822 --> 15:07.616
- We got problems, people!

15:07.616 --> 15:09.201
[tires squealing]

15:10.702 --> 15:12.579
[growling]

15:13.288 --> 15:14.331
[acid sizzles]
[screams]

15:14.331 --> 15:17.709
- No, god! Why did I get
emotionally invested in Desmond?

15:17.709 --> 15:21.755
- Tell my wife I... re-financed
our boat loan.

15:21.755 --> 15:23.757
[growling]

15:24.550 --> 15:27.344
- Uh, okay listen,
if these monsters are really teens,

15:27.344 --> 15:29.179
maybe we can just say things
they don't like.

15:29.179 --> 15:30.222
Did you clean your room?

15:30.222 --> 15:31.098
[shrieks]

15:31.098 --> 15:33.183
- It's working!
What did you do at school today?

15:34.101 --> 15:35.352
Tell me about your classes.

15:35.727 --> 15:38.689
I want to meet your friends.

15:38.689 --> 15:40.983
- Who's gonna accept
my Facebook friend request?

15:40.983 --> 15:42.526
[growling, shrieking]

15:44.778 --> 15:47.197
- Release Little Buddy!
That'll calm the Pupa down.

15:47.781 --> 15:49.616
- This ray has no reverse mode?

15:49.616 --> 15:51.827
- Well, shit, I'm so sorry
I didn't foresee a time

15:51.827 --> 15:54.413
where we would have to turn
a paperweight back into a Little Buddy.

15:54.413 --> 15:58.333
- No, no, no. We have to get Little Buddy
out of there or we screwed!

15:58.333 --> 16:00.419
- We can undo this,
but it won't be easy.

16:00.419 --> 16:02.880
Terry, I'll need you to go to the ship
and activate the de-fractolyzer

16:02.880 --> 16:04.298
which will take at least 12 hours.

16:04.298 --> 16:06.091
After that comes
the really hard part--

16:06.091 --> 16:08.760
[glass shatters]
- Yeah, buddy!

16:08.760 --> 16:10.679
[laughing]

16:10.679 --> 16:12.055
- My bills! Damn it!

16:12.055 --> 16:13.765
I can't remember
how much I owe in dues

16:13.765 --> 16:16.727
to the WGA North for that whole
Ted 3D fiasco!

16:17.394 --> 16:19.354
JESSE:
Little Buddy, come back here!

16:19.354 --> 16:20.647
You're supposed to help us!

16:20.647 --> 16:22.441
- The mistfogsteam
is still everywhere!

16:22.441 --> 16:23.525
[thuds]

16:24.401 --> 16:27.196
- You a-holes better figure
something out real quick!

16:27.196 --> 16:28.322
- This isn't our fault.

16:28.322 --> 16:30.115
- Yeah, we did everything for the Pupa.

16:30.115 --> 16:32.284
He just watched
too many violent video games

16:32.284 --> 16:34.077
and read too many sexy books.

16:34.077 --> 16:36.830
- This is Hollywood's fault!
The Joker! The Joker!

16:36.830 --> 16:39.291
- Let's go get Todd Phillips
and sacrifice him to the steam.

16:39.291 --> 16:41.877
I bet he lives in a Tony Stark-style house
overlooking the bay.

16:41.877 --> 16:43.212
- Will you aliens shut the fuck up?

16:43.212 --> 16:44.463
[growls]

16:44.463 --> 16:46.173
- Venmo me!

16:47.132 --> 16:50.427
- I am so sick of listening
to you blame everyone else.

16:50.427 --> 16:52.012
This is on you.

16:52.012 --> 16:53.096
[all gasp]

16:53.096 --> 16:55.307
- I ship a thicc snack!

16:55.307 --> 16:56.850
[growls]
[all scream]

16:56.850 --> 16:59.394
- The Pupa wouldn't be acting like this

16:59.394 --> 17:01.188
if he had some structure in his life.

17:01.188 --> 17:03.440
He needs present,
tangible role models.

17:03.440 --> 17:05.901
- We see this all the time.
The problem starts at home.

17:05.901 --> 17:07.819
- Home? But that's where we are.

17:07.819 --> 17:12.324
- Oh my god, you are truly
the shittiest parents I have ever met.

17:12.324 --> 17:14.409
Korvo has spent more time
eating me out

17:14.409 --> 17:15.953
than being involved
in the Pupa's education.

17:15.953 --> 17:17.538
- Exactly. Wait, what?

17:17.538 --> 17:19.248
- Well, guess what,
you're fucking wrong,

17:19.248 --> 17:20.624
because we're not human parents.

17:20.624 --> 17:22.084
The Pupa is a member
of our team.

17:22.084 --> 17:23.794
- Do you feed him?
Do you bathe him?

17:23.794 --> 17:26.421
Do you lay in bed at night and worry
he's gonna get run over by a car

17:26.421 --> 17:27.422
or kidnapped by a pervert?

17:27.422 --> 17:31.260
- No, I worry he's gonna get kidnapped
by a car and run over by a pervert,

17:31.260 --> 17:33.303
but now that I'm saying it
out loud, yes.

17:33.303 --> 17:35.013
- Then, honey, you are parents.

17:35.013 --> 17:38.934
All the Pupa does is watch you dumbassses
run around sci-fi'ing shit

17:38.934 --> 17:40.269
with no consequences.

17:40.269 --> 17:41.979
You are the bad influences.

17:41.979 --> 17:45.107
He doesn't have to change,
you do.

17:46.441 --> 17:48.986
- Fuck that. It's not us.
Let's go kill Todd Phillips!

17:48.986 --> 17:50.070
- Woo!
- Yeah, let's get him!

17:50.070 --> 17:51.196
[bellowing]

17:54.032 --> 17:56.326
- Ugh. I hate Earth.
It's a horrible home.

17:56.326 --> 17:58.620
We have to fix the ship.
We're out of Doritos.

17:58.620 --> 17:59.788
Fuck you, Terry.

18:00.622 --> 18:04.710
- Guys, that Supreme steam monster
sounds exactly like us.

18:04.710 --> 18:08.005
- Holy shit. Were we
the Todd Phillips all along?

18:08.005 --> 18:10.507
MONSTER: I want to trap someone
in a paperweight!

18:10.507 --> 18:12.176
- Aw, geez, we suck.

18:12.176 --> 18:14.887
- I can't believe it, but these two
shallow side characters were right.

18:14.887 --> 18:15.929
[laser zaps]

18:18.307 --> 18:20.684
- Regular Hungry Hungry Hippos? Ew.

18:20.684 --> 18:22.019
- Come on,
we have to play. Now!

18:22.019 --> 18:23.061
- Really?
- Yes!

18:23.896 --> 18:26.064
[rattling]

18:26.815 --> 18:28.150
- This is fucking boring.

18:28.150 --> 18:29.484
It was better
when we turned them into--

18:29.484 --> 18:31.111
- Look! What's happening?

18:31.111 --> 18:33.739
- The Pupa is reacting to us
being bland and normal. See?

18:33.739 --> 18:35.824
JESSE:
Oh yeah! I guess it's working.

18:35.824 --> 18:38.160
- From this moment forward,
we have to change our ways.

18:38.160 --> 18:40.370
- So no more awesome sci-fi stuff?

18:40.370 --> 18:42.915
- No. I think we have
to cut everything from our lives

18:42.915 --> 18:45.626
that makes us a special,
unique, weird family

18:45.626 --> 18:48.003
and basically sand
our whole situation down

18:48.003 --> 18:51.465
so it's palatable to a broader,
more corporate-approved audience,

18:51.465 --> 18:52.799
I mean, the Pupa.

18:52.799 --> 18:54.635
- I just signed up for
a Mommy and Me music class

18:54.635 --> 18:55.928
with the Pupa three days a week.

18:55.928 --> 18:57.679
And then I guess we'll go get
no sugar added,

18:57.679 --> 18:59.765
lactose free fro-yo
with the other moms.

18:59.765 --> 19:02.518
- Oh my lilies, he's firming up.
What else can we do?

19:02.518 --> 19:04.645
- We could go back to school
and actually give a shit?

19:04.645 --> 19:06.271
JESSE:
Keep going, keep going!

19:06.271 --> 19:09.942
- Terry and I can get jobs. Real ones.
Not comedy writing or firemen.

19:09.942 --> 19:11.735
Something in an office.
- Yeah. Yeah, yeah, yeah.

19:11.735 --> 19:15.572
With desks. And a computer and a printer
and a receptionist named Gayle

19:15.572 --> 19:17.199
that I keep trying to bang,
but she won't let me hit it!

19:17.199 --> 19:18.742
- We can do this.
For the Pupa!

19:18.742 --> 19:20.244
TERRY/JESSE/YUMYULACK:
For the Pupa!

